<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Software_libraries">Software libraries</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Query_expansion&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Software libraries">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ul><li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://qtanalyzer.codeplex.com/">QueryTermAnalyzer</a> open-source, C#. Machine learning based query term weight and synonym analyzer for query expansion.</li>
<li><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://lucene-qe.sourceforge.net/">LucQE</a> - open-source, Java.  Provides a framework along with several implementations that allow to perform query expansion with the use of Apache <a href="/wiki/Lucene" class="mw-redirect" title="Lucene">Lucene</a>.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Xapian" title="Xapian">Xapian</a> is an open-source search library which includes support for query expansion</li></ul>
